Based Terms Used for Investment

The most big mistakes for the invest starter is to analyze the chart without any insight on the company or coins.
The price of the stock is related with how much company is earning right now or will earn.

1. The starter
  Let's leanrn about the term : Revenue, Operating Profit, and Net Profit

  Imangine that your company sells some product.
  If your company get 100milions from your customer by selling your product. => The term "Revenue" is 100milion for this case.

  But,
  Your company should pay 70milions for 
    1) Salary for the employers
    2) Marketing fee
    3) Development fee
    4) Rental fee for the building
  So your company eventually get 30milions. => The term "Operating Profit" is 30milion for this case.
  
  But,
  Your company should pay 10milions for
    1) Interest for Bank
    2) Tax
  So your company finally get 20milions => The term "Net Profit" is 20milions for this case.
  
  To summarize,
  ① Revenue
    => how much company sell their products.
    => ex) 10miliion, 20miliion.
    If it is going higher and higher => it is good signal for the stock.
  
  b) Operating Profit
    => how much money they really earned from selling the product
    => ex) 10miliion, 20milion.
  
  c) Net Profit
    => How much monty they make a profit


